Get amendments history

Source: R/mica.dars.R
mica.dar.amendments.history.Rd

Get the history of the amendments of a specific data access request.

Usage

mica.dar.amendments.history(mica, pid, df = TRUE)

Arguments

mica

A Mica object

pid

Data access request identifier

df

Return a data.frame (default is TRUE)

See also

Other data access requests functions: mica.dar(), mica.dar.actions(), mica.dar.agreements(), mica.dar.amendment(), mica.dar.amendment.form(), mica.dar.amendment.history(), mica.dar.amendments(), mica.dar.form(), mica.dar.history(), mica.dar.preliminaries(), mica.dar.preliminary(), mica.dar.preliminary.history(), mica.dars()

Examples

if (FALSE) { # \dontrun{
m <- mica.login("someuser", "somepassword", "https://mica-demo.obiba.org")
mica.dar.amendments.history(m, "12345")
mica.logout(m)
} # }
